Fill a #large pot{} with water, add @salt{0.5%tsp}, and bring to a boil. Add @pasta{4%oz} and cook until al dente, about ~{8%minutes}. Drain and set aside.

In a #skillet over medium heat, add @olive oil{2%tbsp} and swirl to coat. Add @tofu{8%oz} cubes and cook until golden on all sides, about ~{6%minutes}. Add @garlic{2%cloves} and saut√© until fragrant, about ~{1%minute}.

In a blender or small pot, combine @cashews{0.25%cup} with @unsweetened almond milk{1%cup} and blend until smooth. Stir in @nutritional yeast{2%tbsp}, @lemon juice{1%tbsp}, @salt{0.25%tsp}, and @black pepper{0.25%tsp} to form the creamy sauce.

Pour the creamy sauce into the skillet with the tofu and simmer briefly to thicken, about ~{2%minutes}. Add the drained pasta and toss to coat, until everything is well combined and heated through, about ~{2%minutes}. --